Message.Title: Android Apps - Only Available to Some Phones & Tables
Message.Msg: Many Android smart phones and tablets are not supported by Google Play. Google restricts apps (both free and paid) to customers that buy products made or approved by Google. Users can't even buy apps directly from the developers. Example: My wife's Coby Tablet runs Android 4.0.3 but Coby didn't pay Google for access to Google Play so I can't buy "TuneIn Radio". Same issue for smart phones. Developer loses the sale because Google can't rip off the manufacturer and the consumer. This is not a technical issue. I'm going to buy the wife an iPad. Where are the consumer groups and the DOJ (restraint of trade)? Google should get sued over this anti-competitive behavior.
